  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka defeated India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lankan women's team won the third Twenty20 International against the Indian women's team.",
        "Sri Lanka, who had already lost the first two matches of the three-match series and lost the series, took a consolation victory in the third match in Dambulla today.",
        "India: 138/5 (20 overs) (Batting: Harmanpreet Keller IE 39 (33), Jemima Rodriguez 33 (30), Smriti Mandana 22 (21), Sappineni Mehhana 22 (26), Pooja Wasrakar 13 (06) Bowling: Oshadi Ranasinghe 1/13 [3], Ama Kansana 1/22 [4], Sukandika Kumari 1/28 [4], Inoka Ranaweera 1/31 [4])",
        "Sri Lanka: 141/3 (17 overs) (Batting: Samari Athappattu IE 80 (48), Nilakshi de Silva 30 (28), Harshita Samarawickrama 13 (14) Bowling: Renuka Singh 1/27 [4], Harmanpreet Keller 0/13 [2], Shefali Verma 0/4 [1])"
      ],
